{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Dough","content":["Lightly grease a large bowl with vegetable oil and set aside.","Place water and yeast into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>1 min\/37°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add flour, salt, sugar, yoghurt and oil and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> or until well combined, then knead <nobr>3 min\/<\/nobr>.","Transfer dough into prepared bowl, cover with a kitchen towel and set aside to prove in a warm place until doubled in size (approx. 50 minutes). Clean and dry mixing bowl. Meanwhile, prepare filling."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place almonds, sugar, raisins, coconut and cream into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>30 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr> or until a paste forms.","Knock down dough, then transfer onto a silicone bread mat or lightly floured work surface.","Divide into 6 equal portions (approx. 120 g each) and shape into a ball. Make a shallow indent in the centre of each ball with your thumb. Place 1½ tablespoons of almond mixture into indent. Pull edges of dough together to enclose filling, pinch to seal and reshape into a ball. Using a rolling pin, roll each ball, into an oval (approx. 22 cm long).","Set a plate aside. Place a large frying pan over high heat. Working 1 naan at a time, place into frying pan and cook until dark brown blisters form (approx. 1-1½ minutes each side). Remove naan from heat and place onto the plate. Then brush with ghee and sprinkle with extra coconut (optional). Transfer onto a serving dish and cover to keep warm. Repeat frying, brushing and sprinkling with remaining naan. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Dough","content":["2 tbsp vegetable oil, plus extra for greasing","190 g water","1 ½ tsp dried instant yeast","450 g baker's flour","1 tsp salt","1 tsp sugar","90 g Greek-style natural yoghurt"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["100 g blanched almonds","3 tsp brown sugar","3 tsp raisins","1 ¼ tbsp desiccated coconut, plus extra for sprinkling (optional)","20 g pouring (whipping) cream","ghee, melted, for brushing (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r132077","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-uPsWbCANLs4\/XZavB269wzI\/AAAAAAAAhqY\/NS63WvnvbWcHC06GxsLSZAmSvvMf38ROQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ULp2GoGpm8pgE4Lt.png","title":"Peshwari naan","publishedAt":"2017-07-03T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13.9 g","fat":"27.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"59.4 g","calories":"2296 kJ \/ 546 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl, kitchen towel, silicone bread mat, rolling pin, serving plates, pastry brush, large plate, large frying pan, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["To make your own ghee, please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip.","Baked naans can be frozen. Allow to cool and store in a freezable bag or container, layered between pieces of baking paper. Defrost thoroughly before reheating in a hot oven (220°C). Place the naan on a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) lined with baking paper and sprinkle with a little water and heat until warmed through (approx. 5 minutes)."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}